{
  "texts": [
    "\"Making chips is like building airplanes -it requires a massive infrastructure.",
    "China has struggled to make its own airplanes, and it faces similar, if not greater, challenges in producing its own chips\" (CN1).",
    "The third key imaginary relates to the country's tech culture, favouring quick returns but leading to long-term harm.",
    "OpenAI's ChatGPT, for example, is frequently mentioned as an innovation that has yet to find a parallel in China, sparking critical reflections on why this might be the case.",
    "Many interviewees express frustration at the gap between their aspirations for AI supremacy and the reality of limited groundbreaking advancements."
  ]
}